IMMEDIATE
No.55/4/CF-69
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA
CABINET SECRETARIAT
(Department of Cabinet Affairs)
New Delhi, the 2lst February 1969,
2nd Phalguna 1890.
CORRIGENDUM
Reference this Secretariat Memo. of even number
dated 14th February 1969, regarding assumption of new
offices by certain Ministers/Deputy Ministers,
For entries (v), (xiii), (xiv), (xix), (xx) and
(xxviii) of the Memo., the following shall be substituted:-
(v) Dr. Triguna Sen relinquished Che office
of Minister of Education, and assumed the
office of Minister of Petroleum and Chemicals
and Mines & Metals,
(xiii) Shri I.K. Gojral relinquished the office
of Minister of State in the Departments of
Parliamentary Affairs and Communications,
and assumed the office of Minister of
State in the Ministry of Information &
Broadcasting, and in the Department of
Communications.
(xiv) Shri Jaganath Rao relinquished the office
of Minister of Works, Housing & Supply, and.
assumed the office of Minister of State in
the Ministry of Petroleum and Chemicals and
Mines & Me tals.
(xix) Prof. Sher $ingh relinquished the office
of Minister of State in the Ministry of
Education, and assumed the office of
Minister of State in the Ministry of
Information & Broadcasting, and in the
Department of Communications.
(xx) Shri D.R. Chavan relinqui shed the office
of Deputy Minister in the Ministry of
Labour, Employment & Rehabilitation, and
assumed the office of Minister of State in
the Ministry of Petroleum and Chemicals and
Mines & Metals.
P.T.O.

(xxviii) Sardar Iqbal Singh relinquished the office
of Deputy Minister in the Ministry of Works,
Housing & Supply, and assumed the office of
Deputy Minister in the Depertment of
Parliamentary Affairs, and in the Ministry
of Shipping & Transport.
(R.N. Kalia)
for Cabinet Secretary.
To
Private Secretaries to
All Members of the Council of Ministers.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the Prime
Minister/the Joint Secretary to the Prime Minister/the
Private Secretary to the Prime Minister, for information.
Copy forwarded to the Secretary to the President/
the Secretary to the Vice-President, for information.
Copy forwarded to all Secretaries/Special
Secretaries/Additional Secretaries to he Government
of India/the Chairman, Railway Board/the Secretary,
Planning Commission/the Secretary, Lok Sabha Secretariat/
the Secretary, Rajya Sabha Secretariat the Secretary,
Department of Parliamentary Affairs/the Secretary,
Electien Commission/the Chairman, Unicn Public Service
Commission/Comptroller and Auditor Cencral of India,
for information,
Copy forwarded to all Ministries/Departments of
Government of India/the Lok Sabha Secretariat/the Rajya
Sabha Secretariat, for information.
(R.N. Kalia)
Under Secretary to the Cabinet.
MEHTA!
